<p>My dialog contains a control of type "Edit". I want to set the text of this edit to the file path of a directory say 'MYDIRECTORY'(Path -> 'C:\Program Files\My Directory'). I tried the following,</p>  <pre><code>&lt;Control Id="MyEdit" Type="Edit" X="23" Y="96" Width="150" Height="18" Property="MYPROPERTY" Text="[MYDIRECTORY]" /&gt;  &lt;Property Id="MYPROPERTY" Value="default property value"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>However, This sets the text of MyEdit as "default property value" and not "C:\Program Files\My Directory". How can I make this work ?</p>  <p>Thanks</p>